(43, 10, 21, 19, 94, 9, 9, 'open the eyes of the blind', 'Connection of Sight and Hearing', 'Both passages emphasize the ability to see and hear, questioning the capacity of God to perceive what He has created. John 10:21 refers to the opening of the eyes of the blind, while Psalms 94:9 speaks of the one who formed the eye and ear. This connection highlights the theme of divine perception and capability.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 21, 23, 35, 5, 6, 'open the eyes of the blind', 'Healing and Restoration Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the opening of the eyes of the blind, highlighting a theme of healing and restoration. John 10:21 references the ability to open the eyes of the blind, which aligns with Isaiah 35:5-6''s prophetic vision of such miraculous events.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 21, 40, 11, 5, 5, 'open the eyes of the blind', 'Healing Miracles and Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the miraculous healing of the blind, highlighting Jesus'' authority and divine power. The question in John 10:21 about a devil opening the eyes of the blind connects directly to the miracles listed in Matthew 11:5.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 21, 2, 8, 19, 19, 'open the eyes of the blind', 'Divine Power Recognition', 'Both passages emphasize recognition of divine power. In John, the ability to open the eyes of the blind suggests a divine act, while in Exodus, the magicians acknowledge the finger of God, indicating a similar recognition of God''s authority.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 21, 19, 146, 8, 8, 'open the eyes of the blind', 'Opening Eyes of the Blind', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine power in opening the eyes of the blind. Both passages emphasize the miraculous ability to restore sight, suggesting a link between Jesus'' actions and God''s authority.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 21, 20, 20, 12, 12, 'open the eyes of the blind', 'Connection of Sight and Hearing', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of sight and hearing as divine gifts. John 10:21 highlights the miraculous opening of the eyes, while Proverbs 20:12 states that the Lord made both the seeing eye and hearing ear.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
